                    <p>To use simply activate the plugin and create a new page. In that page add the shortcode <code>[edd-guest-register]</code>.</p>
<p><strong>Shortcode</strong></p>
<p>Some attributes the shortcode will accept are: <code>url</code>, <code>googleplus</code>, <code>twitter</code>, <code>description</code>, <code>terms</code> &amp; <code>terms_url</code> and **<code>payment_status</code>.</p>
<pre>[edd-guest-register url="true|false" googleplus="true|false" twitter="true|false" description="true|false" terms="true|false" terms_url="" payment_status="true|false"]</pre>
<p>** When the <code>payment_status</code> attribute is set to true (default false) the user trying to sign up has to have there purchase status as publish or completed.</p>
<p><strong>Filters</strong></p>
<p>New: wp_new_user_notification() function to overwrite core.</p>
<p>Use filter <code>wp_new_user_notification_html</code> to output email as HTML. It adds <code>wpautop</code>  to the message.</p>
<pre>
add_filter( \'wp_new_user_notification_html\', \'__return_true\' );
</pre>
