="Custom Login Pro">CLP</abbr> by creating custom post_type&#8217;s. Save as many different designs as you like, or use one of the four designs that come with this plugin. One you upload images and/or just CSS you can activate that post and see your beautiful work on your <code>wp-login.php</code> page!</p>
<p>This is a paid upgrade from my free version which you can find on the <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/custom-login/">WordPress repo</a>. The whole plugin was rewritten from the ground up. Custom Login Pro is now utilizing Custom Post Types to save all your designs. Upon activating a post design the <code>post_content</code> or the CSS get written to a CSS file so that the database is never accessed for super fast load times even on shared hosts.</p>
<ul>
<li>The pro version removes <em>all</em> style sheets from the login screen which the free version did not.</li>
<li>The pro version also writes the CSS to a file which allows the page to load the design with out having to access the database!</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Write less CSS for your WordPress login page, Custom Login Pro uses @<a href="http://lea.verou.me/">LeaVerou</a>&#8216;s <a href="http://leaverou.github.com/prefixfree/">prefixfree</a> JavaScript library.</em></p>
<p><big>Current Version: <strong>1.3.3</strong> <em>Last updated: 3/29/13</em></big></p>

