INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (81, 1, '2013-05-08 18:33:24', '2013-05-08 18:33:24', '<p style="font-size: 16px;"><a href="http://greenbookng.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/greenbookng_ceo.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-87" alt="greenbookng_ceo" src="http://greenbookng.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/greenbookng_ceo.jpg" width="100" height="150" align="left" /></a>Given the recent increase in the number of university graduates in our country and the simultaneous increase of unemployment in the job market, young graduates have been challenged into creating jobs rather than waiting for the labour market to offer them one. This, ironically, has created a positive impact on our economy by developing new businesses and increasing the number of entrepreneurs in our country. More entrepreneurs obviously mean more jobs in the future. A country can only experience substantial growth and development when it begins to support small and medium businesses within its territory.</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px;">Nigeria is a country faced with diverse challenges not only in our government, but also in business development, information technology, copyright and piracy laws, and so many other different sectors. These challenges are however giving young people the objective mindset to come up with innovative ideas capable of surpassing our numerous but insignificant challenges. Todays university graduates in Nigeria are no longer equipped with basic academic knowledge in their various discipline, but also the skills and drive they need to tackle the present unemployment situation in the country, by being entrepreneurial.</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px;">Although it is inarguable a fact that entrepreneurship helps develop a nation or country, however if there are no efforts in place to help encourage and sustain small and medium enterprises (SMEs), then the dream of developing the country becomes farfetched. I am one of the few individuals of the strong opinion that more laws and incentives should be to the favour and consideration of SMEs if one really want to experience significant growth and development in ones\' country.</p>
<p style="font-size: 16px;">Green Book Nigeria is simply one of the numerous structures in place to help promote SMEs and business start-ups in Nigeria. It is a platform solely developed with SMEs in mind, as a portal for reaching and connecting with ideal customers, promoting business sites, getting online presence and networking with other businesses and potential investors or stakeholders. I believe these are the basic needs of every SME or start-up and will go a long way in developing a solid foundational structure by which these businesses could become multinationals.</p>
<i style="font-size: 16px;">Josiah Uma</i>
<i style="font-size: 16px;">CEO, Founder Green Book Nigeria</i>', 'Founder\'s Message', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'founders-message', '', '', '2013-05-20 18:48:19', '2013-05-20 18:48:19', '', 0, 'http://greenbookng.com/?page_id=81', 8, 'page', '', 0) ; 
